programme.desc: It is Christmastime in America's national parks. programme.title: Yosemite America's Treasure
programme.desc: Experience Yosemite's breathtaking icons like the granite monoliths El Capitan and Half Dome and behold the splendor of Bridal Veil and Yosemite Falls. Explore Yosemite's deep history as the first land set aside for preservation, and a land that inspired John Muir and photographer Ansel Adams.

programme.title: Lonely Planet: Best Parks Ever - America's National Parks
programme.desc: See where astronauts trained for moon missions and dive miles deep into crystal caves in the best parks that you've never heard of.

programme.title: Mythical Roads
programme.desc: It is springtime in the southern hemisphere of Argentina, and here, we explore the timeless lands of Patagonia. Everywhere you turn, this land of extremes reveals more and more of its stark and rugged characteristics to you. Here, memories are burned into your mind by the second.

programme.title: Smart Travels with Rudy Maxa
programme.desc: Hot-spiced cider and strains of "O Tannenbaum" warm our hearts as we head to Europe for Christmas. Switzerland has a special glow this time of year and we find plenty of good cheer in the bright Christmas markets and toasty ski lodges.

programme.title: Smart Travels with Rudy Maxa
programme.desc: The Swiss Alps reverberate with cowbells, accordions, and laughter. We make our home base in the year-round playground of Interlaken, the "town between two lakes." Then, we sail across glacial Lake Brienz, famous for its beautiful woodcarving.

programme.title: Big Little Footprints
programme.desc: We travel to the Canadian Rocky Mountains for its stunning natural beauty.

programme.title: Family Travel with Colleen Kelly
programme.desc: Grab your winter gear and head to Quebec City where Colleen's family explores the Winter Carnival and the Hotel de Glace, rides down a mountain on a giant snow tube, tries their hand at dog sledding, and savors maple syrup goodies.

programme.title: Curious Traveler
programme.desc: Why is a European Christmas Market also called Weihnachtsmarkt or a Christkindlmarkt? Why do you find Christmas Markets mostly in German-speaking countries? What is the curious history of the Advent Wreath, of Silent Night, and a creepy Christmas character named Krampus? And who is Krapfen?

programme.title: Curious Traveler
programme.desc: You may not be able to live like a royal, but wouldn't it be nice to shop like one? Let's explore the curious world of Royal Warrants, a special designation given to only the best shops and services, literally fit for a king (or queen, or prince, or princess). Kind of like knighthood for a shop.

programme.title: Tom Kerridge Cooks Christmas
programme.desc: A traditional Christmas feast Tom Kerridge style means Turkey, but this is Turkey with a twist. A seasonal spiced orange cake with plum sauce, Christmas pudding ice cream, and festive mulled cider accompany this memorable holiday meal.

programme.title: The Healthy Voyager's Global Kitchen
programme.desc: Carolyn Scott-Hamilton, the Healthy Voyager, demonstrates how to prepare Vegan Chicken Pastry Puffs.

programme.title: The World's Most Expensive Christmas Cruise Ship
programme.desc: The Seven Seas Splendor welcomes you aboard the world's most expensive cruise ship for a joyous Christmas. A very special Christmas show, luxurious dining, fun excursions, and an opulent spa combine to add much cheer to your holiday.

programme.title: Switzerland's Amazing Train Rides
programme.desc: Take a trip up the Pilatus-Bahn, with a maximum gradient of 48% and average gradient of 35%, making it the steepest cog railway in the word.

programme.title: Switzerland's Amazing Train Rides
programme.desc: Join host Jeff Wilson and PBS award-winning photographers and ride through a Swiss Alps train adventure. The wonders of the Alps exhilarate travelers as you travel through stunning scenic routes and the iconic Matterhorn, a 14,600-foot peak that overlooks the charming town of Zermatt, Switzerland.

programme.title: Switzerland's Amazing Train Rides
programme.desc: Go sightseeing on the Glacier Express, an extraordinary railway journey high into the Swiss Alps across 291 bridges, through 91 tunnels, and across the Oberalp Pass at the highest point (2,033 meters, or 6,670 feet, above sea level), and, visit the iconic Matterhorn on the Gornergrat-Bahn.

programme.title: Mexico One Plate at a Time with Rick Bayless
programme.desc: "You are what you eat." Brillat Savarin's statement fuels Rick's tour of the 21 de Noviembre market in downtown Oaxaca. We uncover the incredibly rich culture of the market and its role in the daily lives and meals of the local population.

programme.title: Mexico One Plate at a Time with Rick Bayless
programme.desc: At Hartwood restaurant, Chef Eric Werner explains the fascinating farm-to-table supply chain that provides Hartwood's live-fire kitchen with fresh ingredients. The rustic simplicity inspires Rick to shop for produce and cook up a storm.

programme.title: Mexico One Plate at a Time with Rick Bayless
programme.desc: Over a breakfast of tortas, Rick and his daughter, Lanie, plan an all-day torta marathon in Mexico City. Their quest begins at the city's charming Sunday flea market, Lagunilla, where they check out some simple, yet mouthwatering tortas.

programme.title: Mexico One Plate at a Time with Rick Bayless
programme.desc: Mexico's beaches glimmer with pristine perfection. Chef Rick Bayless takes us off the beaten path to find great food and even better beaches such as Playa Chahue and Playa Principal. You would be well-advised to follow his lead.

programme.title: Backroads USA
programme.desc: The Mohawk Trail is deeply embedded in the history of America. For many years it served as a main trade route for indigenous tribes. As European settlement expanded, the Mohawk Trail began to change as the country itself changed. Tap into one of America's richest springs of historical significance.

programme.title: Backroads Europe
programme.desc: Open your ears to those who call this land home, and who will unveil its unique characteristics to you. Via Publicae was once an ancient Roman road and trade route that stretched from Braga in the north to Lisbon in the south of Portugal. Roman influence was once very strong in this region.

programme.title: Mythical Roads
programme.desc: Russia's "Far East," known for its extreme geographical situation and climate, is very much like visiting America's Wild West. Here, we explore the Amur River, the border between China and Eastern Russia, along with its basin to the north in the rugged Vladivostok region.

programme.title: Secrets of the National Parks
programme.desc: Discover the secrets of the Southwest along famous Route 66 and the Grand Circle, an area concentrated with national parks. Discover how Monument Valley in Utah and Gallup in New Mexico became cinematic locations, jet-ski in Lake Powell, and explore the spirit of the Navajo in Canyon de Chelly.

programme.title: Traveling with Denella Ri'chard
programme.desc: Rhone River with Denella Ri'chard.

programme.title: Family Travel with Colleen Kelly
programme.desc: From Florida to California, Colleen's family shares their favorite moments from Season 5. They take you back to Chickasaw Country, reminisce about the dude ranch in Tucson, and marvel at the collosal Grand Canyon.

programme.title: Elizabeth Stanton's Great Big World
programme.desc: There are myriad ways to have fun in the Bahamas, and Elizabeth, Taylor, Jennifer, and Rob reveal places you must visit. The four also go deep-sea fishing, feed wild stingrays, dive underwater in unique submersibles, and go ocean tubing.

programme.title: Travels with Darley
programme.desc: Your revolutionary road trip in South Carolina with Darley continues. From Charleston to Camden, the state's two oldest cities, you will learn much more about the founding of America, and its true potential, through the lens of history.

programme.title: Travels with Darley
programme.desc: Our revolutionary road trip in New Jersey with Darley continues as we immerse ourselves in colonial times through interactive history with local experts and follow in George Washington's footsteps. This is where history takes center stage.

programme.title: Tastes Like Home
programme.desc: Catherine meets with Lilian Parkes in Belfast's verdant Botanic Gardens before travelling to Johannesburg to meet her best friend Laura where the two will experience myriad facets of South African life, culture, and cuisine.

programme.title: The Healthy Voyager
programme.desc: Carolyn Scott-Hamilton showcases the best of Oahu and Paso Robles including prime locations to stay, exceptional sites to visit, and unique restaurants specializing in plant-based vegan food that will satisfy the healthy traveler in you.

programme.title: The Healthy Voyager's Global Kitchen
programme.desc: Carolyn Scott-Hamilton, the Healthy Voyager, demonstrates how to prepare a Vegan Shepherd's Pie.

programme.title: Tom Kerridge's Proper Pub Food
programme.desc: Tom prepares decadent, show-stopping dishes for special occasions, including an elegant asparagus served with his ultimate salad dressing, a slow-roast duck, deep-fried oysters, spiced monkfish, and a refreshing gin and tonic granita.

programme.title: My Greek Table with Diane Kochilas
programme.desc: Humble beans and legumes are among the most ancient foods in Greece that have helped sustain Greek civilization from prehistoric times to the present day. Diane invites us into her kitchen to cook three enticing Greek bean dishes.

programme.title: River Cottage Forever
programme.desc: Eager to secure fishing rights to the cottage's lake, Hugh makes a wager with his landlord Antony Hichens: If Hugh can prepare a meal of carp that satisfies Antony and his guests, then Hugh shall have fishing rights to the property's lake.

programme.title: Beyond River Cottage
programme.desc: There are new arrivals on Hugh's farm this spring, including 11 piglets and two baby lambs. Hugh also attends an Easter Blossom Picnic Party, goes mushroom hunting for morells, and gets a crash course in breadmaking from a master baker.

programme.title: Lonely Planet: Best Parks Ever - America's National Parks
programme.desc: Want to release your inner cowboy? These are the western capitals of the world. From the wild buffalo to the beautiful sunsets, these are the best parks ever to star in your own western.

programme.title: Lonely Planet: Best Parks Ever - America's National Parks
programme.desc: This episode features two main attractions: beautiful sunrises and amazing waterfalls. You'll never find more stunning places for rises and falls.

programme.title: Christmas in Americas National Parks
programme.desc: It is Christmastime in America's national parks. Yosemite, Yellowstone, Grand Teton, and Grand Canyon National Parks each offers Christmas visitors their own unique versions of comfort, joy, and the warmth of vintage lodges during the holiday season in the form of festive activities and gatherings.

programme.title: Discovering the World
programme.desc: Lebanon's fertile valleys and archaeological sites bear witness to the country's historical importance. The country's will to live has never ceased to amaze. Despite devastation in numerous conflicts, Lebanon, country of cedar, has always risen again with pride, with Beirut being a striking example.

programme.title: Discovering the World
programme.desc: Set to a backdrop of skies buzzing with aircraft, this is legendary St. Barts, an island that has successfully combined traditions with modernism, and remains a premier destination. This documentary was captured with great affection for this special destination, and it will shine through.

programme.title: Bare Feet with Mickela Mallozzi
programme.desc: The Asian American and Pacific Islander (AAPI) community is a beautifully diverse group of cultures, and Mickela gets a taste of the Pacific Islands around the boroughs by experiencing Na Pua Mai Ka Lani Nuioka, Soh Daiko, Taiko, and more.

programme.title: Xtreme Tourist
programme.desc: Xtreme in Jackson Hole means skiing without snow on roller skis and surviving in the wilderness like a mountain man. programme.title: Steven Raichlen's Project Smoke
programme.desc: Get an inside look at the tools and fuels for creative smoked ribs!

programme.title: Hotels ByDesign
programme.desc: In episode 1 we begin with peak New York accommodation in the heart of Times Square itself. The Tempo, by Hilton, is a hotel that seeks to reflect the energy of time square and an ethos of exploration and discovery. Next Sara takes us to Ontario for our story on Elora Mill, one-of-a-kind bespoke accommodation, perched atop the thundering Elora Gorge amid stunning panoramic views. Then join us at the enchanting Ashford Castle - where Ireland’s history meets opulence, world-class service and unique experiences. We fly back to Chicago for some warm and stylish midwestern hospitality with our story on the Royal Sonesta Chicago Downtown. And finally, we’re off to Croatia for a lesson in “mindful luxury”. Executive Producer Mike Chapman investigates the alchemy between the personal and professional, a stunning location, sincere respect for the environment and chic contemporary design that makes Maslina Resort so special.

programme.title: Hotels ByDesign
programme.desc: Episode 2 of Hotels ByDesign opens with the ultimate oceanfront urban escape at Prince Waikiki. Located at the gateway to urban Honolulu, discover the ingredients that have made this hotel a raging success! Then, get reacquainted with the natural cycles of nature and simpler times as Adam Rolston leads a story on Southall Farm & Inn in the rolling hills of Franklin Tennessee. Travel to India to explore the unique details of The Leela Palace: New Delhi, a true muse of the city's multifaceted legacy. Next, Executive Producer Mike Chapman discovers a collection of Chalets, with breathtaking views of Mt Blanc - L’Alpaga Resort in Megeve. The episode is capped by a story, presented by Scott Henderson about Wentworth Mansion in Charleston - where passion for restoring and revitalizing historical spaces is on full display.

programme.title: Hotels ByDesign
programme.desc: Hotels ByDesign Episode 3 opens with Cameron House on Loch Lomond, a 17th-century Baronial mansion, deeply rooted in the Scottish landscape and boasting exceptional elegance and breathtaking views. Then Brian Brown presents a story on Alila Napa Valley; a serene retreat designed to engage the senses and immerse guests in the California landscape. Mike Chapman takes us to Boutique Hotel Alhambra & The Historic Villas, located on the enchanting island of Lošinj, Croatia. This story explores how distinctive architectural flair and commitment to preserving cultural heritage makes this such a revitalizing destination. We showcase the award-winning French Quarter Inn in Charleston and keep the southern charm rolling with Grand Hotel - “America’s Summer Place” since 1887 - in Mackinac Island, Michigan. Grand Hotel beckons guests to a bygone era of old-world hospitality and charm.

programme.title: Hotels ByDesign
programme.desc: Episode 4 opens with Hotel 11 in Calgary - the first MOD Collection by Sonesta hotel overlooking The Rocky Mountains. Then, the award-winning Spectator Hotel in Charleston; a high-design, distinctive boutique hotel for the well-heeled traveler. Next, a revamped modernist style hotel built in the 1950s, weaving along the coast of the French Riviera - Les Roches Rouges. Hotel Zachary is located in the heart of Chicago’s Lakeview neighborhood - inspired by designs of world-renowned Wrigley Field architect Zachary Taylor Davis. Finally, discover a jewel on the bank of the majestic lake Pichola in Udaipur, India. The Leela Palace Udaipur is spectacular in its architecture and boasts a veritable gallery of traditional artwork in its interior.

programme.title: Hotels ByDesign
programme.desc: A sensational opening to Episode 5 with Atlantis The Royal in Dubai, featuring world-renowned design and breath-taking views of the Dubai skyline and Arabian Sea. Then, Sublime Comporta, a luxurious resort in Portugal where time stands still, and nature presides. Next, immaculately restored 19th Century Zero George in Charleston, South Carolina. Architect Ma Ry Kim explores 1 Hotel Hanalei Bay, the oceanfront sanctuary on Kauaʻi’s North Shore in Hawaii. And finally, we are transported to another place and time with the Titanic Hotel in Belfast. Remember, you can vote for your favorite project for the Sonesta People’s Choice Award now at bydesign.global.

programme.title: Hotels ByDesign
programme.desc: Episode 6 opens in Mauritius with the architecturally striking LUX* Grand Baie - a beachside resort with distinctive modernist design. Then we showcase Hotel Le Moulin - a boutique hotel that encapsulates the enchanting essence of Village Life in the heart of Luberon, Provence. Next, the first hotel to open on Washington DC’s Capitol Hill in 40 years - The Royal Sonesta Washington DC Capitol Hill, pushing the limits. A hotel located in a restored Book Tower Building, ROOST Detroit exemplifies an extended-stay hotel created with high-design and architectural flair at the forefront. Finally, a five-star water-front stay in Croatia awaits. Hotel Ambasador Split offers a travel experience rich in ancient architecture and experiences, off-the beaten-path.

programme.title: Hotels ByDesign
programme.desc: Episode 7 opens with The Leela Palace Jaipur - a pivotal landmark set against the majestic backdrop of the Aravalli range in Udaipur, India. Next Ballyfin Demesne, Ireland’s most lavish Regency mansion. Then Hemlock Neversink invites you to unwind, reconnect, and rest in the Catskills, New York. We showcase The First Collection Jumeirah Village Circle, representing the epitome of urban resort living in the vibrant heart of Dubai. Finally, a former prison transformed into a place of tranquility: The Interlude has become an urban retreat, immersed in Melbourne’s eclectic and creative culture.

programme.title: Hotels ByDesign
programme.desc: Our season finale opens in Nice, Cote D'azur, offering high-end glamour and luxury and views of the Mediterranean sea.
